quran[118]{c,v,t}:
  23,1,Believers will succeed
  23,2,"[This means] those who are reverent in their prayer"
  23,3,who refrain from idle talk
  23,4,"who are active in [promoting] public welfare"
  23,5,and who guard their private parts
  23,6,"except with their spouses and whomever their right hands may control, since then they are free from blame"
  23,7,Those who hanker after anything beyond that are going too far
  23,8,And those who preserve their trusts and their pledge
  23,9,and who attend to their prayers
  23,10,will be the heirs
  23,11,who shall inherit Paradise to live there forever
  23,12,We created man from an extract of clay
  23,13,then We placed him as a drop of semen in a secure resting-place
  23,14,"Then We turned the semen into a clot; next We turned the clot into tissue; and then We turned the tissue into bones and clothed the bones with flesh. Then We reproduced him as a fresh creation. Blessed be God, the Best of Creators"
  23,15,Then later on you shall die
  23,16,Next you will be raised up again on Resurrection Day
  23,17,We have created seven orbits above you; We have not been heedless about creation
  23,18,"We send down water from the sky in due measure, and let it trickle into the earth. We are even Able to make it disappear"
  23,19,We have produced date groves and vineyards on it for you; from which you have much fruit to eat
  23,20,"as well as a tree growing on Mount Sinai which produces oil and seasoning for those who [want to] eat"
  23,21,"You have [still another] lesson in livestock: We let you drink what is in their bellies, and you have many [other] uses in them; some of them you eat"
  23,22,while on them and on shipboard are you transported
  23,23,"We sent Noah to his folk, and he said: \"My people, worship God; you have no other deity except Him. Will you not do your duty"
  23,24,"The elders among his folk who disbelieved said: \"This is only a human being like yourselves who wants to attain some superiority over you. If God had wished, He would have sent down angels [instead]. We never heard about this from our early forefathers"
  23,25,"He is only a man possessed by some sprite, so try to catch him off guard for a moment"
  23,26,"He said; \"My Lord, support me in view of how they have rejected me"
  23,27,"So We inspired him: \"Build the ship under Our eyes and through Our inspiration. When Our command comes and the reservoir bursts open, send two out of every species on board as well as your own family, except for any of them against whom the Sentence has already been pronounced. Do not lecture Me about those who have done wrong: they will be drowned"
  23,28,"When you and anyone else who is with you have boarded the ship, then SAY: \"Praise be to God, Who has saved us from such wicked folk"
  23,29,"And (also) SAY: \"My Lord, land me through a blessed landing; You are the best Harbormaster!\" Unnamed Messengers"
  23,30,"In that there were signs: We are always Testing (people)"
  23,31,Then We produced a generation of others after them
  23,32,"We sent a messenger around from among themselves: \"Serve God; you have no other deity except Him! Will you not do your duty"
  23,33,"The elders among his people who disbelieved and denied there would be any meeting in the Hereafter, even though We had granted them every luxury during worldly life, said: \"This is only a human being like yourselves; he eats what you eat, and drinks what you drink"
  23,34,"If you obey a human being just like yourselves, you will then turn out to be losers"
  23,35,"Does he promise you that when you die and have become dust and bones, that you will be brought forth again"
  23,36,"Away, off with whatever you are threatened with"
  23,37,"There exists only our present life; we die even as we live, and shall not be raised up again"
  23,38,"He is only a man who has invented some lie about God, and we do not believe in him"
  23,39,"He said: \"My Lord, support me because they have rejected me"
  23,40,"He said: \"Some morning soon they will feel regretful"
  23,41,The Blast really caught them and We turned them into rubbish. Away with such wicked folk
  23,42,Then We raised up other generations after them
  23,43,No nation may anticipate its deadline nor will they ever postpone it
  23,44,"Then We sent Our messengers one after another. Each time its messenger came to some nation, they rejected him, so We followed some of them up with others and turned them into conversation pieces. Away with any folk who will not believe"
  23,45,Next We sent Moses and his brother Aaron with Our signs and clear authority
  23,46,"to Pharaoh and his courtiers, and they acted too proudly and were such haughty folk"
  23,47,"So they said: \"Are we to believe in two human beings like ourselves while their people are slaving for us"
  23,48,"They rejected them both, and so eventually were wiped out"
  23,49,Yet We had given Moses the Book so that they might be guided
  23,50,"We set up the son of Mary and his mother as a sign, and sheltered them both on a hilltop where there was both lodging and a spring"
  23,51,"messengers, eat wholesome things and act honorably; I am Aware of anything you do"
  23,52,"This nation of yours [forms] one community while I am your Lord, so heed me"
  23,53,"Yet they carve up their business into cartels among themselves, each faction happy with whatever lies before them"
  23,54,Leave them in their excitement for a while
  23,55,Do they reckon that We have only afforded them wealth and children because of it
  23,56,"We hurry good things up for them, yet they do not even notice it"
  23,57,Those who feel anxious out of awe for their Lord
  23,58,and those who believe in their Lord´s signs
  23,59,and those who do not associate anything with their Lord
  23,60,and those who give away anything they may give while their hearts feel wary lest they should return to their Lord
  23,61,"[all] those compete in doing good deeds and they will soon attain them"
  23,62,We only assign a soul something it can cope with. Before Us lies a Book which speaks up for Truth; they will not be dealt with unjustly
  23,63,Instead their hearts are full of excitement because of this. They have other deeds besides those which they are committing
  23,64,"so that whenever We seize their high-livers with torment, just imagine how they bellow"
  23,65,"Do not roar [so loud] today; you will not be supported by Us"
  23,66,My signs have already been recited to you while you proudly turned on your heels
  23,67,"away from it, sitting up nights to chatter on and on about it"
  23,68,"Have they not reflected on the Sentence, whether something that never reached their earliest forefathers may not have come to them"
  23,69,Or do they not recognize their Messenger and are disgusted with him
  23,70,"Or do they say: \"Some [mad] sprite possesses him!\"? Rather he has brought them the Truth, while most of them hate the Truth"
  23,71,"If Truth had followed their whims, Heaven and Earth would have collapsed in chaos, along with anyone who is in them. Rather We have brought them their Reminder, yet they keep avoiding their Reminder"
  23,72,"Or are you asking them [to make] some outlay´? Your Lord´s tribute is best, for He is the Best Provider"
  23,73,"You are calling them to [follow] a Straight Road"
  23,74,while those who do not believe in the Hereafter go swerving off the Road
  23,75,"Even if We showed them mercy and removed any trouble that worries them, they would still blindly persist in their arrogance"
  23,76,"We had already seized them with torment yet they did not surrender to their Lord nor beseech [Him]"
  23,77,"until just as We opened up a gate for them leading to severe torment, why they were dumbfounded by it"
  23,78,"He is the One Who has furnished you with hearing, eyesight and vital organs; yet how seldom are you grateful"
  23,79,"He is the One Who has scattered you over the earth, and to him shall you be summoned"
  23,80,He is the One Who gives life and brings death; He controls the alternation between night and daylight. Will you not reason
  23,81,Instead they say the same thing as the first men said
  23,82,"they say: \"When we have died and become dust and bones, will we be raised UP again"
  23,83,"This was promised us and our forefathers long ago. These a only legends (made up] by primitive people"
  23,84,"SAY: \"Who owns the earth and anyone on it, if you know [anything]"
  23,85,"They will say : \"It is God´s.\" SAY: \"Will you not bear it in mind"
  23,86,"SAY: \"Who is Lord of the Seven Heavens and Lord of the splendid Throne"
  23,87,"They will say: \"They are God´s.\" SAY: \"Will you do not your duty [by Him]"
  23,88,"SAY: \"In Whose hand lies sovereignty over everything? He protects, while against Him there is no protection, if you but realized it"
  23,89,"They will say: \"It is in God´s.\" SAY: \"How is it you act so bewildered?\"´"
  23,90,Rather We have brought them the Truth while they deny it
  23,91,"God has not adopted any son, nor is there any [other] deity alongside Him, otherwise each god would carry off whatever it has created, and some of them would gain the upper hand over others. Glory be to God beyond what they describe"
  23,92,"Knower of the Unseen and the Visible: Exalted is He over anything they may associate [with Him]"
  23,93,"SAY: \"My Lord, will you show me what they are threatened with"
  23,94,"My Lord, do not place me among such wrongdoing folk"
  23,95,We are Able indeed to show you whatever We are threatening them with
  23,96,Repay evil with something that is finer; We are quite Aware of anything they describe
  23,97,"SAY: \"My Lord, I seek refuge with You from the devils promptings"
  23,98,"I seek refuge with you, my Lord, lest they accompany me"
  23,99,"since whenever death comes to any one of them, he says: \"My Lord, send me back"
  23,100,"so I may act honorably with anything I may have left behind\"´ Indeed not! It is merely a remark he is making. Beyond them there lies a barrier till the day when they will be raised up again"
  23,101,"Once the Trumpet is blown, no ties of kinship will exist between them on that day, nor may they question one another"
  23,102,Those whose scales are heavy will be prosperous
  23,103,while those whose scales are light will be the ones who have lost their souls; they will remain in Hell
  23,104,The fire will scorch their faces while they will glower away in it
  23,105,Were My signs not recited to you as you (all) were rejecting them
  23,106,"They will say: \"Our Lord, our misery has overwhelmed us and we were errant folk"
  23,107,"Our Lord, get us out of here! If we ever should return [to disobedience], then we would indeed be wrongdoers"
  23,108,"He will say: \"Sink down into it, and never speak to Me"
  23,109,"A group of My servants used to say: ´Our Lord, we believe, so forgive us and have mercy on us; You are the Best One to show mercy!´"
  23,110,You took them for a laughingstock until they made you forget to remember Me since you had been laughing so hard at them
  23,111,I have rewarded them today for how patient they have been; they are triumphant
  23,112,"He will say [further]: \"How many years did you stay on earth"
  23,113,"They will say: \"We stayed a day or part of a day. Ask the timekeepers"
  23,114,"He will say: \"You only lasted a little while, if you only realized it"
  23,115,Did you reckon We have created you just for fun and that you would never be returned to Us
  23,116,"Exalted is God, the true King! There is no deity except Him, Lord of the Noble Throne"
  23,117,"Anyone who appeals to any other deity along with God (Himself), has no proof for it. His reckoning rests only with his Lord. Disbelievers will not succeed"
  23,118,"SAY: \"My Lord, forgive and show mercy! You are the Best One to show mercy"